<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4890592>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 4. Hippasteria heathi USNM holotype USNM 22338. Scale bar = 1.0 cm for all unless otherwise specified.A, abactinal surface. B, close-up showing spines and pedicellariae. Length of each pedicellariae equals 3.0 mm. C, actinal surface. D, marginal plates showing spines and pedicellariae. E, Hippasteria falklandica MNHN IE-2006-1165. Actinal surface. F, abactinal surface. G, close-up showing madreporite, spines, and pedicellariae. Length of each pedicellariae equals 3.0 mm. H, marginal plate series showing spines and pedicellariae." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4890592/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4890588>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 2. Hippasteria californica CASIZ 101825, Monterey Bay. Scale bar = 1.0 cm for all unless specified otherwise. A, abactinal surface. B, actinal surface showing furrow and oral regions. C, marginal plates. D, CASIZ 185563 British Columbia, shallow water morphology. Abactinal surface. Scale bar = 0.5 cm. E, actinal region showing furrow spines, inferomarginal plates and spines, actinal pedicellariae. F, CASIZ 113375 British Columbia. Abactinal−lateral view showing abactinal spines, marginal plates. G, CASIZ 113374 British Columbia. Marginal plates, showing spines and pedicellariae." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4890588/files/figure.png" .

